{
    "source": "Technology Guide", 
    "text": "<p>Each suit of technological armor has a full description, including a set of abbreviated statistics. This information is organized as follows.</p>", 
    "type": "section", 
    "name": "Armor", 
    "sections": [
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This is the cost in gold pieces to purchase the suit of armor if it's available for sale. As with magic armor, a technological suit of armor can be sold by PCs for half this value.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Price"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>The weight of the armor in pounds. Weight figures are for armor sized to fit Medium characters. Armor fitted for Small characters weighs half as much, and armor fitted for Large characters weighs twice as much.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Weight"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This indicates if the suit is light, medium, or heavy armor.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Type"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>The protective value of the armor. This armor bonus is added to the wearer's Armor Class.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "AC"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This number is the maximum Dexterity bonus that this type of armor allows.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Max Dex"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This lists the armor check penalty of the suit of armor.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Penalty"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This indicates the armor's arcane spell failure chance.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Spell Failure"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This lists a character's adjusted speed while wearing the armor. Adjusted speeds for characters with base speeds of 20 ft. and 30 ft. are included.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Speed"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>The armor's charge capacity is listed here. If the armor doesn't use energy, this entry is omitted.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Capacity"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This value lists the number of charges the armor consumes over time while activated. (Activating powered armor is a standard action, and deactivating is a free action.) The charge is immediately spent at the beginning of the duration, and any time remaining when the armor is deactivated is lost. </p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Usage"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This describes the armor's appearance, powers, and abilities.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Description"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>Certain requirements must be met for a character to craft a suit of technological armor. These requirements generally consist of having a feat and access to a manufacturing facility.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Construction"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This is the Craft DC required to create the armor. It is also the Knowledge (engineering) DC to correctly identify the armor.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Craft"
        }, 
        {
            "source": "Technology Guide", 
            "text": "<p>This is the cost in gold pieces to create the technological item. Generally, this cost is equal to half the price of the armor.</p>", 
            "type": "section", 
            "name": "Cost", 
            "sections": [
                {
                    "text": "<table class=\"table\">\n<caption>Technology Guide Armor</caption>\n<thead>\n<tr><th>Light Armor</th><th>Price</th><th>Armor/Shield Bonus</th><th>Max. Dex Bonus</th><th>Armor Check Penalty</th><th>Arcane Spell Failure Chance</th><th>Speed (30 ft.)</th><th>Speed (20 ft.)</th><th>Weight</th><th>Capacity</th><th>Usage</th></tr>\n</thead>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Heavy weapon harness</td><td>9,000 gp</td><td>+1</td><td>+6</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>10 lbs.</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Scatterlight suit (brown)</td><td>100 gp</td><td>+1</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Chameleon suit</td><td>15,000 gp</td><td>+2</td><td>+6</td><td>0</td><td>10%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>50</td><td>1 charge/minute</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Scatterlight suit (black)</td><td>150 gp</td><td>+2*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Inssuit</td><td>19,250 gp</td><td>+3</td><td>+6</td><td>0</td><td>15%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>10 lbs.</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Deep diving suit</td><td>26,000 gp</td><td>+3</td><td>+5</td><td>-2</td><td>30%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>20 lbs.</td><td>25</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Scatterlight suit (white)</td><td>200 gp</td><td>+3*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Smart armor (compact form)</td><td>16,500 gp</td><td>+4</td><td>+4</td><td>-2</td><td>25%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>20 lbs.</td><td>60</td><td>1 charge/10 minutes</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Scatterlight suit (gray)</td><td>700 gp</td><td>+4*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Scatterlight suit (green)</td><td>1,000 gp</td><td>+5*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Scatterlight suit (red)</td><td>1,400 gp</td><td>+6*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Scatterlight suit (blue)</td><td>3,600 gp</td><td>+7*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Scatterlight suit (orange)</td><td>6,000 gp</td><td>+8*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Scatterlight suit (prismatic)</td><td>12,000 gp</td><td>+9*</td><td>+8</td><td>-1</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Gravity suit</td><td>40,000 gp</td><td>Varies</td><td>+8</td><td>0</td><td>5%</td><td>30 ft.</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>5 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n<tr><th colspan=\"11\">Medium Armor</th></tr>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Panic suit</td><td>2,000 gp</td><td>+2</td><td>+2</td><td>-4</td><td>50%</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>15 ft.</td><td>2 lbs.</td><td>10</td><td>1 charge/hour, disposable</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>HEV suit</td><td>61,000 gp</td><td>+4</td><td>+3</td><td>-4</td><td>40%</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>15 ft.</td><td>20 lbs.</td><td>25</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Nanite ablative armor</td><td>10,000 gp</td><td>+4</td><td>+4</td><td>-3</td><td>20%</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>15 ft.</td><td>35 lbs.</td><td>24</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n<tr><th colspan=\"11\">Heavy Armor</th></tr>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Spacesuit</td><td>90,000 gp</td><td>+7</td><td>+0</td><td>-8</td><td>50%</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>15 ft.</td><td>35 lbs.</td><td>25</td><td>1 charge/hour</td></tr>\n<tr class=\"even\"><td>Smart armor (expanded form)</td><td>16,500 gp</td><td>+8</td><td>+1</td><td>-5</td><td>35%</td><td>20 ft.</td><td>15 ft.</td><td>20 lbs.</td><td>60</td><td>1 charge/10 minutes</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n<tr><th colspan=\"11\">Shields</th></tr>\n<tbody>\n<tr class=\"odd\"><td>Hard light shield</td><td>6,400 gp</td><td>+2</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>0</td><td>10%</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>&mdash;</td><td>1 lb.</td><td>20</td><td>1 charge/minute</td></tr>\n</tbody>\n<tfoot>\n<tr><td colspan=\"11\">* The full bonus applies only to touch AC. See item for details.</td></tr>\n</tfoot>\n</table>", 
                    "type": "table", 
                    "name": "Technology Guide Armor", 
                    "source": "Technology Guide"
                }
            ]
        }, 
